India Takes 164-Run Lead Over West Indies in Series-Opening Cricket Test

-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 
2011-06-22T00:28:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/india-takes-164-run-lead-over-west-indies-in-series-opening-cricket-test.html
India  took a 164-run lead in the
series-opening cricket Test after dismissing West Indies for 173
and reaching 91-3 in its second innings.  Rahul Dravid, who was dropped when on 6, moved to 45 not
out at stumps on day two to help top-ranked India take control
of the match at Sabina Park in Kingston,  Jamaica .  With three days remaining, India has seven wickets in hand
to set West Indies a victory target and try to bowl out the home
team again for a 1-0 lead in the best-of-three series.  Fast bowlers Ishant Sharma and Praveen Kumar earlier
finished with three wickets apiece as the West Indies slumped to
173 all out after resuming at 34-1.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  